      "doc": "plan",
      "anchor": {
        "heading": "Summary",
        "blockText": "2. **Issue B — Hover content shift**: The `:hover` rule on `li.task-item` applies `padding: var(--space-1) var(--space-2)` which is a four-side shorthand, replacing the idle state's `padding-right: 24px` (reserved for the absolutely-positioned `+` button) with the much smaller `var(--space-2)` (8 px). The resulting right-padding reduction narrows the text column, reflowing wrapping text. Fix: explicitly carry `padding-right: 24px` into the hover rule.",
        "line": 12
      },
      "comment": "test",
      "status": "pending",
      "createdAt": "2026-05-27T13:07:48.178Z"
